<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-01T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 Wong Bock Yue/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-01T20:00:00+08:00">August 1, 1930—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 1—4:43 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>651. Department’s 239, July 17, 7 p.m. Legation is today informed through
                            the Diplomatic Bureau that the authorities Garrison Headquarters state
                            food, drink, sleeping and living quarters of Garrison Headquarters house
                            of detention are sanitary and that no discrimination exists in case of
                            Wong Bock Yue.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>